When previewing the README.md file of a given repo (&#x27;Overview&#x27; tab), the inline backticked text sits slightly above the other words in the paragraph, which makes expressions look faintly like a highlighted superscript of some kind.

The difference appears better at some zoom-levels than others, as it&#x27;s only slightly off base (see attachment). Although my system picks up Courier from the {{font-family:}} style, I have confirmed this is not a font-issue by using the web-console to try other fonts.

The CSS-rule that seems to be the culprit is

{code:CSS}
ak-editor-bitbucket .code, code, tt {
  padding: 1px 3px;
  [...]
}
{code}

Platform: Firefox 56.0 and Chrome 61.0.3163.100 on Windows 7 Enterprise

Chrome example:

!173248605-chrome%20example.png|thumbnail!

Performing an AWS CodeDeploy results in a 500 internal server error. I have replaced parameters for security purposes

https://codedeploy.bitbucketconnect.com/deployment?jwt=TOKEN&deployment_group=Staging-Deploy&commit_like_id=SC-1757&repo_uuid={UUID}&repo_url=http://bitbucket.org/repo/repo.git

{code}
#!text
Internal Server Error

The server encountered an internal error ormisconfiguration and was unable to completeyour request.

Please contact the server administrator at root@localhost to inform them of the time this error occurred, and the actions you performed just before this error.

More information about this error may be availablein the server error log.
{code}

*Current behaviour / steps to reproduce:*

Take the following setup into consideration:

* users: {{john@lorem.com}} and {{alice@ipsum.com}}
* group: {{lorem-contributors}}
* project: {{builder}}
* repo: {{web}}

User {{alice@ipsum.com}} is not part of any group / doesn&#x27;t have access to any project / any repo / any group (except {{stash-users}} for login access).

User {{john@lorem.com}} is a member of group {{lorem-contributors}}\\
Group {{lorem-contributors}} has {{PROJECT_WRITE}} access to project {{builder}} (so they can create Pull Requests).

When user {{john@lorem.com}} creates a PR, he can mention {{@al}} in the PR&#x27;s description field and user {{alice@ipsum.com}} will be displayed, even if she doesn&#x27;t have any access to the project / repo / group.

*Expected behaviour:*

When mentioning users in the Pull Request description field, only users that have access to that repo / project should be displayed as autocomplete suggestions.
